Tuckahoe School Drama Club students have continued to work tremendously hard during the time of school building closure. They rehearsed for several weeks, attended regular group rehearsals, and each individually recorded videos of two songs from our musical production of Aladdin, Jr. These individual recordings were then combined to create two spectacular music videos, featuring the entire participating cast.

Enjoy their videos!!!

https://tinyurl.com/TuckahoeDramaSong1

post_text:
Buenos Días,

El governador Cuomo ha anunciado que las escuelas continuarán estar cerradas hasta e incluyendo el catorce de abril.

Durante este tiempo, cuando estamos enseñando de una distancia, usando varios métodos y maneras de enseñar, continuaremos seguir con el calendario del distrito. Las lecciones continuarán sin interrupción hasta el tres de abril.

Dicho eso, el calendario del distrito tiene vacaciones de primavera desde el seis hasta el diez de abril.

Durante las vacaciones de primavera, los estudiantes NO tienen que continuar con sus lecciones.
Durante las vacaciones de primavera, los maestros NO tienen que enviar más lecciones.
Las lecciones continuarán empezando el 13 de abril.

Se les continuarán distribuir comida durante este período, inclusivo durante las vacaciones de primavera.

post_text:
Governor Cuomo has just announced that schools are to remain closed up to and including April 14th.
During this time, while we are teaching in a blended learning environment via distance learning platforms, we will continue to follow the district calendar. Lessons will continue without interruption until April 3rd.

However, our district calendar provides for Spring Recess April 6th through April 10th.
During Spring Recess students are NOT expected to continue their lessons.
During Spring Recess teachers are NOT expected to send any new lessons.
Lessons will continue beginning Monday, April 13th.

Delivery of meals will continue throughout this period, including during Spring Recess.

post_text:
Tuckahoe School Teachers miss their students SOOOOOOOOO much that they are having a Tuckahoe School Parade of cars! Mrs. Sanders, our art teacher, has organized our teachers to meet at 10 am tomorrow, Thursday, March 26th to drive through our neighborhoods and wave to our kids.

Safety is of course our first priority, so we are asking you to follow these ground rules:
1. Complete social distancing must remain in place.
2. Wave from your doors and windows
3. Do not approach the cars.

We miss you and love you but for everyone’s safety we must remain at a distance.

So, here are the details:

When: Thursday, March 26, 2020 at 10 am

Where: From the school, we will follow the North and South bus routes. (see the map and directions provided.

THIS IS VERY EXCITING!

Buenas Tardes,

Soy Jamie Pajan, de parte de Len Skuggevik, Superintendente del Distrito Escolar Común de Tuckahoe. Debido al orden dado por el Ejecutivo del Condado de Suffolk, El Distrito Escolar Común de Tuckahoe será cerrada para dos semanas, empezando el 16 de marzo hasta el 27 de marzo. Como indicado en el mensaje antes, nuestro programa de educación remota empezará el 17 de marzo, 2020.

Todos miembros de la facultad y el personal tienen que irse su oficina o clase a la hora normal para finalizar planes y para recoger materiales. No habrá ninguna reunión.

Horarios de trabajo e instrucciones para el personal serán notados antes del fin del día de trabajo el dieciséis de marzo.

Otra vez, gracias por su cooperación. Sean seguros y sanos.

IMPORTANT MESSAGE FROM LEN SKUGGEVIK, SUPERINTENDENT - MARCH 15, 2020

Good Afternoon,

This is Len Skuggevik, Superintendent of the Tuckahoe Common School District. Due to the emergency executive order just issued by the Suffolk County Executive , Tuckahoe School will now be closed for students for a two week period, from March 16, 2020, through March 27, 2020. As stated in previous message, our remote learning program will begin on Tuesday, March 17, 2020.

All faculty and staff are expected to report to work, and proceed directly to their office or classroom at regular time on Monday, March 16, 2020 to finalize any plans and pick up equipment/materials. There will be no mass gatherings or meetings.

Work schedules and directives for all staff beyond 3/16/2020 will be announced before the end of the work day on 3/16/2020.

Again, thank you for your cooperation. Please be safe and stay healthy.

post_text:
On Friday January 31,2020 Tribal Trustee Germain Smith of the Shinnecock Nation presented the Tuckahoe Common School District with the Shinnecock Nation Flag. Mr. Smith thanked Superintendent Len Skuggevik for the Districts welcoming, community focused transition into the school and for the district’s ongoing efforts to ensure the Nation is a valued part of the Tuckahoe family.
The Tuckahoe Common School District and Shinnecock Nation are in the final stages of creating a contract that would enable the students of the Shinnecock Nation to continue the option of attending the district for at least another five years. The current contract is set to expire in June 30, 2020.

post_text:
TUCKAHOE LOWERS TAXES!
Story:
The Tuckahoe Common School District is proud to announce that it is lowering the 2019-2020 tax levy from the previously approved $19,548,138 to $18,948,138. This is a reduction of $600,000 and equates to a change from a tax increase of 2.9% to a tax decrease of .26%. In addition, we have made the last payment of our energy performance contract, eliminating our long-term debt and saving the taxpayers $41,111 in interest charges over the next 9 years. This has been made possible by maximizing other sources of revenue and monitoring/decreasing spending when possible. We will continue to be fiscally responsible as we provide our students with a quality education.

post_text:
Congratulations to Emma Cervone!
Emma Cervone, 8th grade graduate of Tuckahoe Common School District in Southampton, was 1 of more than 30 students who received medals of honor at The Suffolk County Legislature’s Distinguished Youth Award ceremony on Wednesday, July 17th, 2019. The award promotes and recognizes achievement, initiative and volunteer service. As a recipient of the gold award, the highest level of achievement in the program, Emma worked with an adviser and local officials to complete goals in volunteer service, personal development, physical fitness challenges as well as exploration of Suffolk County Parks totaling more than 400 hours of service over the course of 1 year. These four areas challenged her to become active in her community and surroundings while learning skills to help achieve goals that will be used throughout her life!
